  <sect2 role="package">
    <title>Introduo a c-ares</title>

    <para>
      <application>c-ares</application> is a C library for asynchronous DNS
requests.
    </para>

    &lfs113_checked;

    <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Informao do Pacote</bridgehead>
    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Transferncia (HTTP): <ulink url="&c-ares-download-http;"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Transferncia (FTP): <ulink url="&c-ares-download-ftp;"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Soma de verificao MD5: &c-ares-md5sum;
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Tamanho da transferncia: &c-ares-size;
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Espao em disco estimado exigido: &c-ares-buildsize;
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Tempo de construo estimado: &c-ares-time;
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Dependncias de c-ares</bridgehead>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Exigida</bridgehead>
    <para role="required">
      <xref linkend="cmake"/>
    </para>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Instalao de c-ares</title>

    <para>
      Instale <application>c-ares</application> executando os seguintes comandos:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>mkdir build &amp;&amp;
cd    build &amp;&amp;

cmake  -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr .. &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      This package does not include a test suite.
    </para>

    <para>
      Agora, como o(a) usurio(a) <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem>:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>



